other_tests.findings: Dense vitritis in the right eye. Examination showed no peripheral retinal infiltrates but a suggestion of subretinal purulent material.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Initial finding of vitritis improved to 20/400 visual acuity five days post-vitrectomy and continued to improve to 20/60 at nine months.

other_tests.findings: Numerous red blood cells, shock of wheat crystals, suggesting sulfadiazine crystalluria.
